  "prompt": "How do I stop my Labrador/Pug mix from humping my pillows?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help stop your dog from humping pillows:\n\n1. Behavioral interventions:\n- Redirect the behavior when it starts\n- Use a firm \"No\" command\n- Provide alternative activities or toys\n- Distract with play or training\n\n2. Potential underlying causes:\n- Excess energy\n- Anxiety or stress\n- Hormonal issues\n- Learned behavior\n\n3. Practical solutions:\n- Increase exercise and physical activity\n- Provide mental stimulation\n- Keep pillows out of reach\n- Consider spaying/neutering if not already done\n\n4. Training techniques:\n- Positive reinforcement\n- Consistent training\n- Teach \"leave it\" command\n- Reward calm behavior\n\n5. Professional help:\n- Consult a veterinarian to rule out medical issues\n- Work with a professional dog trainer if behavior persists\n\n6. Long-term management:\n- Establish consistent boundaries\n- Maintain regular exercise routine\n- Provide plenty of attention and interaction\n\nRemember, patience and consistency are key when addressing behavioral issues.",
